240, 349, 534\n|y5= 15, 20, 23, 35, 39, 51, 87, 116, 164, 209, 321, 384, 460, 586, 643\n|y1Title=France\n|y2Title=Italy\n|y3Title=Spain\n|y4Title=Germany\n|y5Title=UK\n|yGrid= |xGrid= \n}}\n\n== Responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic, and criticism ==\n===Timeline larger European state interventions===\n<div style=\"text-align:center;\">{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/201903 timeline large European state interventions}}</div>\n\n===Criticism===\nAlthough by 7 March some European politicians such as France's [[Marine Le Pen]] had called for Europe's internal borders to be temporarily closed,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |title=Coronavirus: European borders likely to remain open despite crisis in Italy, observers say |date=7 March 2020 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315040544/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the [[European Union]] by 13 March continued to reject the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Area|Schengen free travel area]] and introducing border controls with Italy.<ref name=\"dw-schengen\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313142436/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure |date=25 February 2020 |work=Bloomberg |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227122244/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173409/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |title=Commission chief warns against unilateral virus travel bans |date=13 March 2020 |work=[[EURACTIV]] |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195056/https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The deputy leader of the Swiss [[Ticino League]], Lorenzo Quadri, by 29 February had criticised the decision: \"It is alarming that the dogma of wide-open borders is considered a priority.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream |date=26 February 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303055756/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> United States President [[Donald Trump]] said by 12 March the European Union had \"failed to take the same precautions and restrict travel from China and other hot spots\" as the US had implemented.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |title=In dramatic step, Trump restricts travel from Europe to US to fight coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140433/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Trump also said that \"As a result a large number of new clusters in the United States were seeded by travellers from Europe.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: What you need to know about Trump's Europe travel ban |url=https://www.thelocal.dk/20200312/trump-imposes-travel-ban-from-europe-over-coronavirus-outbreak |work=The Local |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> Research on [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|coronavirus genomes]] indicates the majority of COVID-19 cases in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] came from European travelers, rather than directly from China or any other Asian country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Studies Show N.Y. Outbreak Originated in Europe|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/coronavirus-live-updates.html |work=The New York Times |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n\nBy 9 March Czech Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] stated that \"European countries cannot ban the entry of Italian citizens within the Schengen area. The only possible way is to have the Italian prime minister call on his fellow citizens to refrain from traveling to other countries of the European Union.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |title=Czech PM: Italians Should Be Banned From Travelling Due to Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=SchengenVisaInfo.com |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171345/https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland and Denmark announced complete closure of their national borders, the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said by 12 March that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization. Moreover, they have a strong social and economic impact, they disrupt people\u2019s lives and business across the borders.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314202823/https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> European Union leaders condemned the US decision to restrict travel from Europe to the United States. [[European Council]] President [[Charles Michel]] and Ursula von der Leyen said in a joint statement: \"The European Union disapproves of the fact that the US decision to impose a travel ban was taken unilaterally and without consultation.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |date=12 March 2020 |work=Associated Press (AP) |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313140528/https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ursula von der Leyen admitted by 17 March that \"all of us who are not experts initially underestimated the coronavirus.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |title=Politicians 'underestimated' virus threat, von der Leyen admits |date=18 March 2020 |work=Euractiv |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319152350/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Italian government has criticised EU's lack of solidarity with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |title=The EU Is Abandoning Italy in Its Hour of Need |date=14 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315112947/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |date=11 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313000621/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Italy wonders where Europe's solidarity is as coronavirus strains show |date=13 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315154437/https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |title=Italy criticizes EU for not responding its call for help, 'only China responded bilaterally' |date=12 March 2020 |work=CGTN |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316024124/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Politico'' reported on 7 March that \"EU countries have so far refused Italy's plea for help fighting coronavirus, as national capitals worry that they may need to stockpile face masks and other medical gear to help their own citizens, officials and diplomats said.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |title=Europe fails to help Italy in coronavirus fight |date=7 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317055659/https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Maurizio Massari, Italy's ambassador to the EU, said that \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\" /> [[Serbia]]n President [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] said that \"European solidarity does not exist. That was a fairy tale.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |title=China is winning the coronavirus propaganda war |date=18 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203919/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n[[File:Reivindicaciones 8M (49637966373).jpg|thumb|[[International Women's Day]] march in M\u00e9rida, Spain, 8 March<ref>{{cite news |title=Thousands March in Spain on Women's Day Despite Coronavirus Fears |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-08/thousands-march-in-spain-on-womens-day-despite-coronavirus-fears |date=8 March 2020 |work=[[US News]] |agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>]]\nAccording to ''The Guardian'', [[Spain]]'s initially slow response to the coronavirus caused the epidemic to become severe even though it did not share a land border with Italy or other severely affected countries.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tremlett |first1=Giles |title=How did Spain get its coronavirus response so wrong? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/26/spain-coronavirus-response-analysis |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> An analysis in ''[[Vox (website)|Vox]]'' hypothesised that the minority government did not want to risk its hold on power by banning large gatherings early; Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] initially defended his decision to allow large gatherings to continue.<ref name=Vox>{{cite news |last1=Ward |first1=Alex |title=How Spain's coronavirus outbreak got so bad so fast |url=https://www.vox.com/2020/3/20/21183315/coronavirus-spain-outbreak-cases-tests |work=Vox |date=20 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe planned [[NATO]] \u201c[[List of NATO exercises|Defender 2020]]\u201d military exercise in Germany, Poland, and the Baltic states,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |title=How coronavirus derailed the largest Nato exercise in 25 years |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Spectator |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102257/https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the largest NATO war manoeuvres since the end of the [[Cold War]], was to be held on a reduced scale because of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |title=NATO scales down exercises due to coronavirus |date=19 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102254/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]'s general secretary [[Kate Hudson (activist)|Kate Hudson]] critisiced the Defender 2020 exercise: \"In the current public-health crisis, it jeopardises the lives not only of the troops from the US and the many European countries participating but the inhabitants of the countries in which they are operating.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |title=Nato must end 'dangerous and irresponsible' military exercise on Russia's border, campaigners say |date=18 March 2020 |work=Morning Star |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320010441/https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"OKOpress_Szumowski_EU_claims\">{{cite news | last1= Pa\u0144kowska | first1= Maria | language =pl | title= Szumowski krytykuje UE: 'Nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci'. To wielopi\u0119trowy fa\u0142sz |trans-title = Szumowski criticise the EU: 'There is no European solidarity'. Which is false at many levels<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 2020-03-26 |newspaper= [[OKO.press]] | url= https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |quote= Bo jak by\u015bmy czekali na inne kraje, na Europ\u0119, na \u015bwiat, to by\u015bmy si\u0119 obudzili bez \u015brodk\u00f3w, a dooko\u0142a wszyscy by te \u015brodki sobie zakupili ... \u017beby by\u0142a jasno\u015b\u0107, to nie jest tak, \u017ce my ten sprz\u0119t mamy w Europie, \u017ce s\u0105 jego nieograniczone ilo\u015bci. ... Bo niestety tutaj centralne zakupy zawiod\u0142y, nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci.  |accessdate=2020-03-26 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326225848/https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |archivedate= 2020-03-26 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://systems.jhu.edu/research/public-health/ncov/ ncov \u2013 CSSE] \u2013 Map of the expansion of the virus in Europe and in the world\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 disasters in Europe|coronavirus outbreak]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Europe}}\n{{About|the pandemics in the continent|the pandemic in the political and economic union|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the European Union}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe\n| image           = Persons died due to coronavirus COVID-19 per capita in Europe.svg\n| caption         = Cumulative number of deaths per million inhabitants from COVID-19 in Europe.<ref name=\"coronacount\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries |title=Coronavirus update (live) |date=20 March 2020 |website=www.worldometers.info |url-status=live |access-date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322140128/https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries |archive-date=22 March 2020 }}</ref><!-- Date and legend inside image -->\n| map2            = Red COVID-19 Outbreak Cases per capita in Europe.svg\n| legend2         = Confirmed cases of SARS-CoV-2 infected people in relation to the population of the country (cases per million inhabitants).<ref name=\"coronacount\"/> The numbers are not comparable, as the testing strategy differs between countries and time periods. |link=Special:FilePath/Coronavirus_infected_persons_per_capita_in_Europe.svg \n| map3            = COVID-19 death per infected in Europe.svg\n| legend3         = Number of deaths per 100 confirmed COVID-19 infected inhabitants in Europe.<ref name=\"coronacount\" /><!-- Date and legend inside image -->\n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = Europe\n| first_case      = [[Bordeaux]], France\n| arrival_date    = 21 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=21|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China<ref name=\"20200130cdc\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/summary.html |title=2019 Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Summary |date=30 January 2020 |website=[[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC) |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126210549/https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/summary.html |archive-date=26 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 1,084,230<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\n| recovery_cases  = 316,992<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\n| deaths          = 156,215<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\n| suspected_cases = \n| territories     = 57<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=locations}}\n\n{{As of|2020|03|13|post=,}} the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) considered Europe the active centre of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|<noinclude>2019\u201320 coronavirus </noinclude>pandemic]]. Cases by country across Europe had doubled over periods of typically 3 to 4 days, with some countries (mostly those at earlier stages of detection) showing doubling every 2 days.<ref>[https://ourworldindata.org/coronavirus Max Roser, Hannah Ritchie and Esteban Ortiz-Ospina (2020) \u2013 \"Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) \u2013 Research and Statistics\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319171947/https://ourworldindata.org/coronavirus |date=19 March 2020}} 13 March 2020, ''ourworldindata.org/coronavirus'', accessed 14 March 2020</ref>\n\n{{As of|2020|03|17|alt=As of 17 March|post=,}} all countries within Europe had a confirmed case of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], with [[Montenegro]] being the last European country to report at least one case.<ref>[https://twitter.com/MeGovernment/status/1239992049350447104 Two COVID-19 cases confirmed in Montenegro] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317191704/https://twitter.com/MeGovernment/status/1239992049350447104 |date=17 March 2020}} ''twitter.com/MeGovernment'' accessed 17 March 2020</ref> At least one death has been reported in all European countries, apart from the [[Vatican City]].\n\n{{As of|2020|03|18|alt=As of 18 March|post=,}} more than 250&nbsp;million people are in lockdown in Europe.<ref>{{cite news |last=Henley |first=Jon |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/coronavirus-lockdown-eu-belgium-germany-adopt-measures |title=More than 250m in lockdown in EU as Belgium and Germany adopt measures |date=18 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |issn=0261-3077 |access-date=4 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401085742/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/coronavirus-lockdown-eu-belgium-germany-adopt-measures |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Risk assessment for the pandemic in the EU/EEA and UK ==\nAs of 17 March 2020, there had been 2,740 reported deaths in the EU/EEA and UK from COVID-19<ref name=ECDC>{{cite web |url=https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/cases-2019-ncov-eueea |title=Situation update for the EU/EEA and the UK |date=13 March 2020 |website=www.ecdc.europa.eu |access-date=15 March 2020 <!--08:00--> |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304105320/https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/cases-2019-ncov-eueea |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> (25 March number: 10,049).\n\nOn 13 March 2020, the following COVID-19 related risks were assessed by the ECDC:<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/current-risk-assessment-novel-coronavirus-situation |title=Daily risk assessment on COVID-19, 13 March 2020 |date=13 March 2020 |website=www.ecdc.europa.eu |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305021409/https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/current-risk-assessment-novel-coronavirus-situation |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Risk\n! Level\n|-\n| risk of severe disease associated with COVID-19 infection for people in the EU/EEA and UK: general population\n| moderate  \n|-\n| risk of severe disease associated with COVID-19 infection for people in the EU/EEA and UK: older adults and individuals with chronic underlying conditions\n| high\n|-\n| risk of milder disease, and the consequent impact on social and work-related activity,\n| high\n|-\n| risk of the occurrence of sub-national community transmission of COVID-19 in the EU/EEA and the UK\n| very high\n|-\n| risk of occurrence of widespread national community transmission of COVID-19 in the EU/EEA and the UK in the coming weeks \n| high\n|-\n| risk of healthcare system capacity being exceeded in the EU/EEA and the UK in the coming weeks\n| high\n|-\n|risk associated with transmission of COVID-19 in health and social institutions with large vulnerable populations \n| high\n|}\n\n== Statistics by country and territory ==\n{{Main|Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data}} \n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Europe medical cases chart}}\n[[File:COVID-19-Europe-selection-relative-deaths-log.svg|thumb|600px|Cumulative number of deaths per million inhabitants for a selection of European countries, over time. The legend is sorted in descending order of these values. Logarithmic vertical axis. Data source: [[ECDC]].<ref name=ECDC/>]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|+Summary table of confirmed cases in Europe (as of 20 April 2020)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/ |title=Tracking SARS-CoV-2: Map, data and timeline |last=News |first=BNO |date=18 February 2020 |website=BNO News |access-date=4 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207094017/https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/ |archive-date=7 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n!Country\n!Confirmed\n!Deaths\n!Recovered\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|ESP}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]]\n|200,210\n|20,852\n|80,587\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200311/mapa-del-coronavirus-espana/2004681.shtml |title=Coronavirus \u2013 El mapa del coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a: m\u00e1s de 2.200 casos, casi la mitad en la Comunidad de Madrid |date=11 March 2020 |website=RTVE.es |language=es |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311221636/https://www.rtve.es/noticias/2020031